- Hosts with cass indexed AND agent data: **pre-selected** (ready to sync)
- Hosts with cass not indexed: **pre-selected** (quick to index)
- Hosts without cass: **not pre-selected** (requires install confirmation)
- Unreachable/already-configured: **not selectable**

### Status Badges (right-aligned)
- `✓ Ready to sync` - cass installed + indexed
- `⚡ Needs indexing` - cass installed, index empty/missing
- `⚠ Needs install` - cass not found
- `✗ Unreachable` - SSH connection failed
- `═ Already setup` - in sources.toml already

## Keyboard Controls

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| ↑/↓ or j/k | Navigate up/down |
| Space | Toggle selection on current item |
| Enter | Confirm selection |
| Esc or q | Cancel |
| a | Select all (selectable hosts) |
| n | Deselect all |
| / | Start search/filter mode |
| Esc (in search) | Exit search mode |

### Search/Filter Mode
For users with many hosts, pressing `/` enters filter mode:
```
┌─ Filter: css_ ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Showing 2 of 12 hosts matching "css"                                      │
│                                                                             │
│  [x] css                                                    ✓ Ready to sync │
│      ...                                                                    │
│  [ ] css-staging                                            ⚠ Needs install │
│      ...                                                                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Implementation

### Data Structures
```rust
pub struct SelectableHost {
    pub probe_result: HostProbeResult,
    pub state: HostState,
    pub selected: bool,
    pub display_lines: Vec<String>,  // Pre-rendered ANSI lines
}

pub enum HostState {
    ReadyToSync,      // cass installed + indexed
    NeedsIndexing,    // cass installed, needs index
    NeedsInstall,     // cass not found
    Unreachable,      // SSH failed
    AlreadyConfigured, // in sources.toml
}

pub struct HostSelectionResult {
    pub selected_hosts: Vec<HostProbeResult>,
    pub hosts_needing_install: Vec<HostProbeResult>,
    pub hosts_needing_index: Vec<HostProbeResult>,
    pub estimated_install_time_secs: u64,
    pub cancelled: bool,
}
```

### Selection UI Function
```rust
pub fn run_host_selection(
    probed_hosts: &[HostProbeResult],
    already_configured: &HashSet<String>,
) -> Result<HostSelectionResult, CliError> {
    // 1. Build selectable items with pre-computed display
    let items = build_selectable_hosts(probed_hosts, already_configured);

    // 2. Apply pre-selection logic
    let items = apply_preselection(items);

    // 3. Run interactive selection
    let selected_indices = run_multiselect(&items)?;

    // 4. Build result
    build_selection_result(&items, &selected_indices)
}
```

### Terminal Width Handling
- Minimum width: 60 chars (truncate hostnames)
- Optimal width: 80+ chars (full display)
- Very narrow: fall back to compact single-line mode

### Non-TTY Fallback
If stdin is not a TTY, provide helpful error:
```
Error: Interactive selection requires a terminal.

For non-interactive use:
  cass sources setup --hosts css,csd,yto
  cass sources setup --non-interactive  # select all reachable
```

