 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-robapica","title":"Capabilities Endpoint (cass capabilities)","description":"# Capabilities Endpoint (cass capabilities)

## Problem Statement
Agents need to know what features are available:
- Does this version support --fields?
- Is aggregation available?
- What connectors are supported?

## Proposed Solution
Add `cass capabilities` command:
```bash
cass capabilities --json
```

Output:
```json
{
  "crate_version": "0.1.30",
  "api_version": 1,
  "contract_version": "1",
  "features": [
    "json_output",
    "jsonl_output",
    "robot_meta",
    "time_filters",
    "field_selection",
    "aggregations",
    "cursor_pagination"
  ],
  "connectors": [
    "codex", "claude_code", "gemini", "opencode", "amp", "cline"
  ],
  "limits": {
    "max_limit": 1000,
    "max_content_length": 100000,
    "max_fields": 20
  },
  "documentation_url": "https://github.com/..."
}
```

## Design Decisions

### Feature Flags
List individual features so agents can check availability:
```python
if "field_selection" in capabilities["features"]:
    cmd += " --fields source_path,line_number"
```

### Version Numbers
- `crate_version`: Semantic version of the binary
- `api_version`: Integer version of the API contract (bump on breaking changes)
- `contract_version`: Existing robot-docs contract version

### Limits
Expose operational limits so agents don't exceed them.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `cass capabilities --json` returns feature list
- [ ] Features list accurately reflects available functionality
- [ ] Version numbers included
- [ ] Limits documented
- [ ] Human-readable output without --json

